%N A393483 For k >= 1, perfect powers A001597(k) for which ratio A001597(k+1) / A001597(k) is smaller than that for any smaller k.
%e A393483 A001597(2)/A001597(1) = 4/1 = 4: a(1) = 1.
%e A393483 A001597(3)/A001597(2) = 8/4 = 2: a(2) = 4.
%e A393483 A001597(4)/A001597(3) = 9/8 = 1.125: a(3) = 8.
%e A393483 A001597(5)/A001597(4) = 16/9 = 1.777...: not smaller than the prevailing minimum.
%e A393483 A001597(6)/A001597(5) = 25/16 = 1.5625: not smaller than the prevailing minimum.
%e A393483 A001597(7)/A001597(6) = 27/25 = 1.08: a(4) = 25.
%o A393483 (PARI) my(r=oo, pprev=1); for(p=2, 10^10, if(!ispower(p), next); if(p/pprev<r, r=p/pprev; print1(pprev, ", ")); pprev=p)
